Event-ScreenSaver

This module gives you an easy way to add a hook to perform actions when the
screen saver is started/stopped. It will try to load the most appropriate
module for monitoring the starting and stopping of the screen saver.
Currently that means the Unix OS module it probably wont work more broadly
than Linux/Unix operating systems.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Event::ScreenSaver

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Event-ScreenSaver

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Event-ScreenSaver

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Event-ScreenSaver

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Event-ScreenSaver/

    Source Code
        http://github.com/ivanwills/Event-ScreenSaver/tree/master

